Entities (SQL tables):

campaign: for campaigns (id, name, etc).

smsgateway: stores SMS API info (api_url, username, password).

sms_number: stores SMS numbers (refs smsgateway).

campaign_number: associates an sms_number with a campaign.

user: stores customer/user info (business name, address, phone, carrier, etc).

campaign_user: links users to campaigns (refs campaign and user).

dne: "Do Not Engage" list (never message these users).

campaign_prefab: pre-fabricated message templates, tied to a campaign.

Core Features:

Create/Edit/Delete campaigns, SMS gateways, SMS numbers, users, prefab messages.

Associate SMS numbers and users with specific campaigns.

Bulk Send a message to all users in a campaign.

Template messages: Allow messages to inject fields from the user table (e.g., {{businessName}}).

DNE Enforcement: Check DNE list before sending any message or responding.

Chat-style interface for incoming/outgoing SMS replies (real-time feel if possible).

Notifications page showing unread or new SMS responses.

Other:

Admin dashboard UI for all tables.

Ensure DNE list checks at every relevant send/receive point.

Prefab messages editable and reusable within campaigns.

Support for reading SMS responses and replying back through the correct SMS gateway and number.

My application provides users with a digital wallet system that serves as a payment method for third-party services. Each user can create one or more wallet accounts within the platform. Each account is independent, with its own balance and transaction history.

Updated functional requirements:

1. User wallet accounts
	•	A user can own multiple wallet accounts.
	•	Each account includes:
	•	A custom name or label (e.g., “Main Wallet”, “Vehicle A”).
	•	An optional account type (e.g., personal, corporate, prepaid).
	•	A status (active, suspended, closed).
	•	Current balance.
	•	Creation date and last updated timestamp.

2. Top-ups (credits)
	•	Wallets support top-ups from various payment methods: credit/debit card, bank transfer, payment gateways, cash.
	•	Recommended metadata:
	•	Top-up amount.
	•	Payment method used.
	•	External transaction reference ID.
	•	Timestamp.
	•	Status: pending, approved, failed.
	•	User who performed the action (for delegated access).
	•	Source IP/device (for traceability).
	•	Optional notes or applied promotions.

3. Payments (debits)
	•	Debit transactions are linked to a specific wallet account.
	•	Recommended fields:
	•	Amount.
	•	Service type (toll, parking, others).
	•	External service reference.
	•	Status (approved, rejected, pending).
	•	Timestamp.
	•	Location or service point (optional).
	•	External system response code/message (for traceability).

4. Transactions / Account statement
	•	Each wallet has its own independent transaction history.
	•	Each transaction should include:
	•	Unique identifier.
	•	Type (credit, debit, refund, hold, adjustment).
	•	Balance before and after the transaction.
	•	Date and time.
	•	Short description.
	•	Actor (who performed the transaction).

5. Additional recommendations
	•	Support for reversals and refunds.
	•	Support for temporary holds on balance (e.g., pending external confirmation).
	•	Full audit trail: created by, modified by, timestamps.
	•	Optional multi-currency support (for future internationalization).

Feature	Description
Bill of Materials (BoM)	Blueprint of a product—defines raw materials, operations, and costs. Multiple BoMs can exist per item.
Work Orders	Used to initiate production. Tracks raw material consumption and finished goods output.
Production Planning Tool	Forecasts and plans production based on demand and stock.
Job Cards	Tasks assigned to workers/stations with operation details, time tracking, and status.
Operations & Workstations	Defines each step (cutting, assembling, painting, etc.) and resources/stations.
Routing	Sequence of operations used for producing items.
Capacity Planning	Checks machine or workstation availability to avoid overloading.
Subcontracting	Manages outsourced operations and raw material transfers to third-party vendors.
Scrap Management	Tracks wastage during production and scrap valuation.
Production Analytics	Built-in reports for efficiency, costs, completion, delays, and throughput.

🔄 Workflow Summary
BoM Creation →
Define the materials and processes for a product.

Work Order →
Create when production is needed (linked to a Sales Order or manually).

Material Request / Stock Entry →
Issue or transfer raw materials to production.

Job Cards →
Assign tasks to workers or machines.

Work Order Completion →
Output finished goods into stock, track scrap, and compute costs.

📊 Reports Available
Work Order Summary

BoM Comparison

Production Analytics

Job Card Time Tracking

Subcontracting Ledger

🔌 Integrations with Other Modules
Module	Integration
Inventory	Real-time tracking of raw material consumption and finished good stock.
Sales	Auto-create Work Orders from Sales Orders.
Purchase	Raise purchase requests for raw materials or subcontracting needs.
Accounts	Cost accounting of manufacturing, scrap valuation, and vendor billing.
HR	Worker time logs and productivity via Job Cards.
